<!-- 
     Schema for the parameters for the WIP Inspection Scrap Quantity Maintenance Business Object
-->
<xsd:schema elementFormDefault="qualified" attributeFormDefault="unqualified" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <xsd:element name="PostWIPInspectionScrap">
    <xsd:annotation>
      <xsd:documentation>This is the root element.</xsd:documentation>
    </xsd:annotation>
    <xsd:complexType mixed="false">
      <xsd:sequence>
        <xsd:element name="Parameters" minOccurs="0">
          <xsd:annotation>
            <xsd:documentation>This element contains the optional parameter elements.</xsd:documentation>
          </xsd:annotation>
          <xsd:complexType mixed="false">
            <xsd:all minOccurs="0">
              <xsd:element name="ValidateOnly" default="N" minOccurs="0">
                <xsd:annotation>
                  <xsd:documentation>If this flag is set to Y then the xml document is validated but the function is not performed at all. NOTE if set then the Apply If Entire Document Valid is ignored. Default to N. Possible values: Y (validate only) or N (validate and update).</xsd:documentation>
                </xsd:annotation>
                <xsd:simpleType>
                  <xsd:restriction base="xsd:string">
                    <xsd:minLength value="0"/>
                    <xsd:maxLength value="1"/>
                    <xsd:whiteSpace value="preserve"/>
                    <xsd:enumeration value="N"/>
                    <xsd:enumeration value="Y"/>
                  </xsd:restriction>
                </xsd:simpleType>
              </xsd:element>
              <xsd:element name="IgnoreWarnings" default="Y" minOccurs="0">
                <xsd:annotation>
                  <xsd:documentation>If this flag is set to N then any warnings given are treated as errors and returned as errors therefore allowing them to be addressed. Default to Y. Possible values: Y (ignore warnings) or N (output warnings as errors).</xsd:documentation>
                </xsd:annotation>
                <xsd:simpleType>
                  <xsd:restriction base="xsd:string">
                    <xsd:minLength value="0"/>
                    <xsd:maxLength value="1"/>
                    <xsd:whiteSpace value="preserve"/>
                    <xsd:enumeration value="Y"/>
                    <xsd:enumeration value="N"/>
                  </xsd:restriction>
                </xsd:simpleType>
              </xsd:element>
              <xsd:element name="ApplyIfEntireDocumentValid" default="N" minOccurs="0">
                <xsd:annotation>
                  <xsd:documentation>If you want to apply the changes only if everything submitted in the document is valid, when processing several inspection references at the same time, this parameter should be set to Y else the function will be applied for each valid item. NOTE it is not advised to set this on to process a single item as it causes the program to pass through the same routines twice. Default to N. Possible values: Y (apply only if everything is valid) or N (apply each valid item).</xsd:documentation>
                </xsd:annotation>
                <xsd:simpleType>
                  <xsd:restriction base="xsd:string">
                    <xsd:minLength value="0"/>
                    <xsd:maxLength value="1"/>
                    <xsd:whiteSpace value="preserve"/>
                    <xsd:enumeration value="N"/>
                    <xsd:enumeration value="Y"/>
                  </xsd:restriction>
                </xsd:simpleType>
              </xsd:element>
              <xsd:element name="TransactionDate" minOccurs="0">
                <xsd:annotation>
                  <xsd:documentation>Date transaction raised. If not supplied, then the system run date is used.</xsd:documentation>
                </xsd:annotation>
                <xsd:simpleType>
                  <xsd:restriction base="xsd:date">
                  </xsd:restriction>
                </xsd:simpleType>
              </xsd:element>
            </xsd:all>
          </xsd:complexType>
        </xsd:element>
      </xsd:sequence>
    </xsd:complexType>
  </xsd:element>
</xsd:schema>
